phases.content:
Add a cargo test that pins serde serialization shape for every struct returned across the Tauri IPC boundary (generalizes #259, which guarded only TikiRelease.archived). Put it in a clear location — either a new `#[cfg(test)] mod ipc_serialization` in commands.rs or a new test module file; match the crate's existing test conventions.

For each struct: build an instance with ALL fields populated (and, for Option fields, also a None-variant where relevant), `serde_json::to_value`, and assert:
- expected camelCase keys are PRESENT (e.g. createdAt, schemaVersion, activeWork, pipelineStep, unresolvedScriptPaths, copyInstallDetected, tagName, isDraft);
- `#[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]` fields: present when Some, ABSENT when None (assert both directions on at least GitHubRelease {name, publishedAt, url} and one IssueContext optional);
- non-optional and `#[serde(default)]` fields: ALWAYS present even when default/false (the #259 invariant — e.g. TikiRelease.archived present when false; DiagnosticsReport.unresolvedScriptPaths present when empty);
- the `#[serde(tag="type")]` WorkContext union serializes `type:"issue"` / `type:"release"`.

Structs to cover (from the scout inventory): TikiRelease, TikiState, WorkContext/IssueContext, TikiPlan, Phase, DiagnosticsReport, ReleaseCheck, GitHubRelease (Some + None variants), GitHubIssue, GitHubPullRequest, GitHubPrDetail, GitHubComment. Read each struct's serde attrs first (state.rs, github/*.rs) so the asserted keys match the actual rename_all/skip rules — do NOT guess; open the structs.

Keep the existing `tiki_release_archived_survives_serialization` test (commands.rs:1362) OR fold its exact assertion into the new test (archived present == true). Run `cargo test --lib` (from apps/desktop/src-tauri, avoids the running-app exe lock) — green. `cargo clippy --lib -- -D warnings` clean for additions.
